d a world that was changing more quickly than they were. This is a story of resilience and idealism, of violence and small-mindedness, of a world that has long disappeared and one that remains with us to this day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zOntariozEast Flamborough. 4aCultural Studies. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aHistory: Military History. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh  a129th Battalion .  a1917 election .  aCanadian Expeditionary Force .  aCanadian history .  aCanadian military history .  aEast Flamborough, Ontario .  aFirst World War .  aOntario history .  aPasschendaele .  aVimy Ridge .  aYpres .  aconscription .  alocal history.  arural Canada .08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112389140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771123891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771123891/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles